Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a large #pot of salted water.

Slice the @potatoes{3} into 1cm rounds.

Pop the sliced potatoes into the boiling water and cook until slightly softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander and set aside. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when just fork tender—take care not to overcook!

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Thinly slice the @mushrooms{125%g}.

Trim the @carrot{1}(chopped into 1cm chunks) (no need to peel).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} to a #bowl along with 2 tbsp @oil{to taste}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and mix together.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g} (cook in two batches if necessary).

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and cook until the chicken is browned, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Add the onion and carrot and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the mushrooms and a little more @oil{to taste} if needed. Turn the heat up slightly.

Cook everything together until the mushrooms are browned, about ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add @water{150%ml} and @chicken stock{1%sachet} to the pan. Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve.

Stir in @mustard{1%sachet}, @Worcester sauce{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{125%g}. Bring back to the boil, then turn down the heat.

Simmer gently until reduced by around one-third, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Loosen with a splash of water if necessary!

Transfer the contents of the pan to an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Top with the cooked potato slices then sprinkle over the breadcrumbs.

Bake on the top shelf of your #oven until the topping is golden brown and chicken is cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve straight from the dish!